title: Cast Away
overview: A FedEx executive undergoes a physical and emotional transformation after crash landing on a deserted island.

title: Les triplettes de Belleville
overview: When her grandson is kidnapped during the Tour de France, Madame Souza and her beloved pooch Bruno team up with the Belleville Sisters--an aged song-and-dance team from the days of Fred Astaire--to rescue him.

title: La vita è bella
overview: When an open-minded Jewish librarian and his son become victims of the Holocaust, he uses a perfect mixture of will, humor, and imagination to protect his son from the dangers around their camp.

title: Jab We Met
overview: A depressed wealthy businessman finds his life changing after he meets a spunky and care-free young woman.

title: Breakfast at Tiffany's
overview: A young New York socialite becomes interested in a young man who has moved into her apartment building, but her past threatens to get in the way.

title: Watership Down
overview: Hoping to escape destruction by human developers and save their community, a colony of rabbits, led by Hazel and Fiver, seek out a safe place to set up a new warren.

title: En man som heter Ove
overview: Ove, an ill-tempered, isolated retiree who spends his days enforcing block association rules and visiting his wife's grave, has finally given up on life just as an unlikely friendship develops with his boisterous new neighbors.

title: Hotaru no haka
overview: A young boy and his little sister struggle to survive in Japan during World War II.

title: Good Bye Lenin!
overview: In 1990, to protect his fragile mother from a fatal shock after a long coma, a young man must keep her from learning that her beloved nation of East Germany as she knew it has disappeared.

title: Majo no takkyûbin
overview: A young witch, on her mandatory year of independent life, finds fitting into a new community difficult while she supports herself by running an air courier service.

title: Coraline
overview: An adventurous 11-year-old girl finds another world that is a strangely idealized version of her frustrating home, but it has sinister secrets.

title: Kaguyahime no monogatari
overview: Found inside a shining stalk of bamboo by an old bamboo cutter and his wife, a tiny girl grows rapidly into an exquisite young lady. The mysterious young princess enthralls all who encounter her, but ultimately she must confront her fate, the punishment for her crime.

title: Kaze tachinu
overview: A look at the life of Jiro Horikoshi, the man who designed Japanese fighter planes during World War II.

title: Le Petit Prince
overview: A little girl lives in a very grown-up world with her mother, who tries to prepare her for it. Her neighbor, the Aviator, introduces the girl to an extraordinary world where anything is possible, the world of the Little Prince.

title: The African Queen
overview: In WWI Africa, a gin-swilling riverboat captain is persuaded by a strait-laced missionary to use his boat to attack an enemy warship.

title: Moonrise Kingdom
overview: A pair of young lovers flee their New England town, which causes a local search party to fan out to find them.

title: Persepolis
overview: A precocious and outspoken Iranian girl grows up during the Islamic Revolution.

title: Hana-bi
overview: Nishi leaves the police in the face of harrowing personal and professional difficulties. Spiraling into depression, he makes questionable decisions.

title: Lage Raho Munna Bhai
overview: Munna Bhai embarks on a journey with Mahatma Gandhi in order to fight against a corrupt property dealer.

title: City Lights
overview: With the aid of a wealthy erratic tippler, a dewy-eyed tramp who has fallen in love with a sightless flower girl accumulates money to be able to help her medically.
